Layered Architecture — strictly enforced
- routers/: Route definitions and input validation ONLY. Delegate to service immediately. Max 20 lines per route handler.
- services/: All business logic. No FastAPI imports — must be testable without the HTTP server.
- helpers/: Pure utility functions. No side effects, no DB, no network. Every helper has a unit test (where practical).
- dependencies/: FastAPI Depends() functions only: get_db, get_current_user, require_role, get_pagination.

Async Rules
- ALL route handlers must be async def
- ALL MongoDB calls must use Motor — never PyMongo sync
- ALL Redis calls must use redis.asyncio
- Never use time.sleep() — use asyncio.sleep()
- Long tasks go in BackgroundTasks

Exception Hierarchy
Services raise domain exceptions. Routers convert to HTTPException.
- NotFoundError → HTTP 404
- PermissionError → HTTP 403
- ConflictError → HTTP 409
- ValidationError → HTTP 422
- MediaUploadError → HTTP 500

